model_completion: Born in 1908, Edward R. Murrow was an American journalist and broadcaster. He was the first director of the United States Information Agency, and is considered to be one of the most influential broadcasters of the 20th century. Murrow was born in Polecat Creek, North Carolina, and moved to Washington, D.C. at the age of 12. He graduated from Washington and Lee University in 1928, and began his career as a radio announcer. In 1935, he joined CBS, and became the network's first war correspondent. He covered the Spanish Civil War, and later the Second World War. In 1953, he was awarded a Pulitzer Prize for his reports on Senator Joseph McCarthy. Murrow was also the host of the television program 'See It Now,' which aired from 1951 to 1958.

Stephanie Kwolek was born in 1923 in New Kensington, Pennsylvania. She attended Carnegie Institute of Technology, now Carnegie Mellon University, and received her Bachelor's degree in chemistry in 1946. She then went on to work for DuPont, where she invented Kevlar, a strong, lightweight material used in bulletproof vests and other products. Kwolek was awarded the National Medal of Technology in 2014.

Harvey Milk was born in 1930 in Woodmere, New York. He was the first openly gay man to be elected to public office in California. Milk was a civil rights activist and a leader of the gay rights movement. He was assassinated in 1978.

Born in 1982, Priyanka Chopra is an Indian actress and singer. She is the winner of the Miss World pageant of 2000. She has appeared in over 50 Bollywood films, and has also starred in American films such as 'Quantico' and 'Baywatch.' She has also released a number of singles, and has won a number of awards, including the National Film Award for Best Actress.

Darius Khondji was born in 1955 in Tehran, Iran. He is a French cinematographer, who has worked on many films, including 'Seven', 'The Talented Mr. Ripley', 'The City of Lost Children', and 'The Sheltering Sky'. Khondji has won several awards, including the Academy Award for Best Cinematography for 'Seven'.

Evo Morales was born in 1959 in the small town of Orinoca, Bolivia. He was the son of a coca farmer, and was raised in a poor family. He was the first indigenous president of Bolivia, and was elected in 2005. He is a member of the Movement Towards Socialism, and is a left-wing politician. He is a supporter of the coca leaf, and has legalized the coca leaf in Bolivia. He is also a supporter of the legalization of marijuana.

George Washington was born on February 22, 1732, in Westmoreland County, Virginia. He was the son of Augustine Washington and Mary Ball Washington. George Washington was a planter and a military leader. He was the commander-in-chief of the Continental Army during the American Revolutionary War. He was also the first President of the United States, serving from 1789 to 1797. George Washington died on December 14, 1799, at his home in Mount Vernon, Virginia.

Frida Kahlo was born in 1907 in Mexico City. She was a Mexican painter, who is best known for her self-portraits. Kahlo's work is often characterized by its unconventional imagery, which is heavily influenced by Mexican culture. She was married to the famous Mexican muralist Diego Rivera. Kahlo died in 1954, at the age of 47.

He is a professor of philosophy at the University of Ljubljana, and a senior researcher at the Institute of Sociology and Philosophy. He is also a visiting professor at the European Graduate School, and a visiting professor at the University of Chicago. He is a prominent philosopher, and a public intellectual. He has written many books, including 'The Sublime Object of Ideology,' 'The Ticklish Subject,' and 'Less Than Nothing.'

Alvin Ailey was born in 1931 in Rogers, Texas. He was the son of a sharecropper and a domestic worker. Ailey began his dance training at the age of 12. He was a member of the New York City Ballet and the American Ballet Theatre. In 1958, Ailey founded the Alvin Ailey American Dance Theater. He was also the artistic director of the company. Ailey died in 1989.

Yuna Kim is a South Korean figure skater. She is the 2010 Olympic champion, the 2009 World champion, and the 2009 Four Continents champion. Kim was born in 1990 in Gyeonggi-do, South Korea. She started skating at the age of 5. In 2005, she won the World Junior Championships. In 2006, she won the World Junior Championships and the Four Continents Championships. Jackie Chan was born in 1954 in Hong Kong. He is a Chinese actor, director, producer, martial artist, and singer. Born in Poland in 1867, Marie Curie was the first woman to win a Nobel Prize. She was also the first person to win a Nobel Prize twice. Curie was a physicist and chemist, and she is best known for her discovery of radium and polonium. She was the first woman to teach at the University of Paris, and she was the first woman to become a professor at the University of Warsaw. Curie died in 1934, at the age of 66.

Karl Marx was born in Trier, Germany, on May 5, 1818. He was a German philosopher, economist, and revolutionary. He is best known for his work 'The Communist Manifesto,' which laid out the basic principles of communism. Marx's ideas have had a huge impact on the world, and his ideas are still relevant today. He died on March 14, 1883.

Rachel Maddow was born in 1973 in Castro Valley, California. She graduated from Stanford University in 1994, and then went on to get her doctorate in politics from Oxford University. She worked as a host on Air America Radio, and then became a host on MSNBC in 2008. She is the host of the show 'The Rachel Maddow Show,' which airs on MSNBC. John Maynard Keynes was born in 1883 in Cambridge, England. He was a British economist, and one of the most influential economists of the 20th century. Keynes was a member of the Bloomsbury Group, a group of intellectuals and artists. He was a professor at Cambridge University, and was a key figure in the formation of the Bretton Woods system. He died in 1946.

Born in 1852, Edward Bouchet was the first African American to earn a Ph.D. degree. He was also the first African American to earn a doctorate in physics. Bouchet was born in New Haven, Connecticut, and was the son of a former slave. He attended Yale University, where he earned his bachelor's degree in 1874. He then went to the University of Heidelberg in Germany, where he earned his Ph.D. in physics in 1876. Bouchet returned to the United States and taught physics at the University of Vermont. He later became a professor at the University of Pennsylvania, where he taught physics and chemistry. He was also the first African American to be appointed to a full professorship at a major university.

Hammurabi was the sixth king of the First Babylonian Dynasty. He was born in 1792 BC and ruled from 1728 to 1750 BC. He was the first king to unite all of Mesopotamia under one ruler. He is best known for his Code of Hammurabi, which was the first written code of law in history. The code was inscribed on a 2.25 meter tall stone stele, which is now on display at the Louvre Museum in Paris.

Albert Einstein was born in Ulm, Germany on March 14, 1879. He was a theoretical physicist who developed the theory of relativity. He received the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1921. Einstein is considered one of the most influential scientists of the 20th century. He died on April 18, 1955 in Princeton, New Jersey.

Ludwig van Beethoven was a German composer and pianist. He was born in Bonn, Germany, in 1770. Beethoven's father was a musician and he taught Beethoven to play the piano. Beethoven's first public performance was at the age of 7. He was a child prodigy. Beethoven's first symphony was performed in 1800. He wrote 9 symphonies, 5 concertos for piano, 32 piano sonatas, 16 string quartets, and other chamber music. Beethoven's most famous works are his 5th and 9th symphonies. Beethoven died in 1827.

Toni Morrison was born Chloe Anthony Wofford on February 18, 1931, in Lorain, Ohio. She was the second of four children. Her parents were George Wofford, a shipyard welder, and Ramah Wofford, a domestic worker. Morrison's parents were both African-American, and her family was poor. She was raised in a working-class neighborhood, and her family was very religious. Morrison attended Lorain High School, and she was the first black student to be admitted to the school's debate team. She graduated from Howard University in 1953, and she received a master's degree in English from Cornell University in 1955. Morrison worked as an editor at Random House, and she published her first novel, 'The Bluest Eye,' in 1970. She has since published many other novels, including 'Song of Solomon,' 'Beloved,' and 'A Mercy.'

Michael Phelps is an American swimmer who has won a total of 22 Olympic medals, 18 of which are gold. He is the most decorated Olympian of all time. Phelps was born in 1985 in Baltimore, Maryland. He began swimming at the age of 7, and by the age of 15, he had won his first Olympic gold medal. In 2008, Phelps won eight gold medals at the Beijing Olympics, breaking the record for the most gold medals won by an individual at a single Olympics. In 2012, he won four gold medals at the London Olympics, and in 2016, he won five gold medals at the Rio Olympics. Phelps has won a total of 28 Olympic medals, 23 of which are gold.

Octavia E. Butler was born in Pasadena, California in 1947. She was the first African-American woman to win a Hugo Award, for her novel 'Kindred.' She was also the first science fiction writer to receive a MacArthur Foundation 'genius' grant. Octavia E. Butler died in 2006.

Christiane Amanpour is a British-Iranian journalist and CNN's chief international correspondent. She was born in London in 1958, and moved to the United States when she was 11. She attended the University of Rhode Island, and later studied journalism at the University of Rhode Island and the University of Southern California. She began her career as a reporter for the Washington Post, and later worked for the New York Times, the Financial Times, and the International Herald Tribune. She joined CNN in 1990, and has covered many major news events, including the Gulf War, the fall of the Berlin Wall, the Rwandan genocide, the September 11 attacks, and the Iraq War. She has won numerous awards, including the Peabody Award, the Alfred I. duPont-Columbia University Award, and the George Foster Peabody Award.

Diego Maradona was born in 1960 in Buenos Aires, Argentina. He is a former Argentine soccer player and coach. Maradona is considered one of the greatest soccer players of all time. He was the captain of the Argentina national team that won the 1986 World Cup. Maradona was also the captain of the Napoli team that won the Serie A title in 1987. He was the FIFA World Player of the Year in 1987 and 1990. Maradona was the first player to be awarded the Golden Ball at the 1986 World Cup. He was also the first player to be awarded the Golden Ball at the 1990 World Cup.

Judy Garland was born Frances Ethel Gumm in 1922. She was the youngest of three children. Her parents were vaudevillians, and they moved the family to California when Judy was 3 years old. Judy began performing at the age of 2, and she was signed to MGM at the age of 13. She starred in many movies, including 'The Wizard of Oz' and 'A Star is Born.' Judy Garland died in 1969 at the age of 47.

Tom Brady is a professional American football player. He was born in 1977 in San Mateo, California. Brady is the quarterback for the New England Patriots. He was drafted by the Patriots in 2000. Brady has won five Super Bowls, and he has been named the Super Bowl MVP three times. He has also won three NFL MVP awards. Brady is married to supermodel Gisele Bundchen. They have two children together.

Kim Kardashian was born in Los Angeles, California in 1980. She is the daughter of the late attorney Robert Kardashian and Kris Jenner. Kim is a socialite, model, and actress. She is best known for her role in the reality TV series 'Keeping Up with the Kardashians.' Kim has also appeared in the films 'Disaster Movie' and 'Deep in the Valley.' She has also released a fragrance and a book. Kim is married to rapper Kanye West, and they have two children together.

Hakeem Olajuwon was born in Lagos, Nigeria in 1963. He moved to the United States at the age of 12, and attended the University of Houston. In 1984, he was drafted by the NBA's Houston Rockets. He was named the NBA's Most Valuable Player in 1994 and 1995, and won two NBA championships with the Rockets in 1994 and 1995. He was inducted into the Basketball Hall of Fame in 2008.

Agatha Christie was born in 1890 in Torquay, England. She was the daughter of an American mother and a British father. She was educated at home by her mother. In 1914, she married Archibald Christie, a British Army officer. During World War I, she worked as a nurse in a hospital in Torquay. In 1920, she published her first novel, The Mysterious Affair at Styles. The novel was a huge success, and she went on to write 66 detective novels and 14 short story collections. Her most famous works include Murder on the Orient Express, And Then There Were None, and The Murder of Roger Ackroyd. Agatha Christie died in 1976.

Elvis Presley was born in Tupelo, Mississippi, on January 8, 1935. He was the fourth of eight children. His parents were Vernon and Gladys Presley. Elvis's musical career began in 1954, when he was signed to RCA Records. His first single, 'That's All Right', was a hit, and he became a major star. Elvis's career was cut short by his death in 1977. He is considered one of the most influential musicians of the 20th century.

Michael Jackson was born in Gary, Indiana, on August 29, 1958. He was the seventh of nine children. His father, Joseph Jackson, was a steel mill worker, and his mother, Katherine Jackson, was a devout Jehovah's Witness. Michael Jackson's first public performance was at the age of 5, when he joined his brothers in a group called the Jackson 5. The group had a string of hits, including "I Want You Back" and "ABC." In 1979, Michael Jackson released his first solo album, "Off the Wall." In 1982, he released "Thriller," which became the best-selling album of all time. Michael Jackson's career was marred by controversy, including allegations of child molestation and plastic surgery. He died on June 25, 2009, at the age of 50.

Paul Farmer is a physician and anthropologist who has worked in Haiti for more than 20 years. He is the co-founder of Partners in Health, a non-profit organization that provides health care to the poor in Haiti and other developing countries. Farmer is also the co-founder of the Haitian Health Foundation, which provides health care to the poor in Haiti. He is the author of 'Pathologies of Power: Health, Human Rights, and the New War on the Poor,' and 'To Repair the World: Paul Farmer Speaks to the Next Generation.'

Milton Glaser was born in 1929 in New York City. He studied at the High School of Music and Art, and the Cooper Union. He is a graphic designer, illustrator, and painter. He is best known for his 'I Love New York' logo, and the Bob Dylan poster. He has designed over 500 posters, and has won numerous awards. He is the founder of the School of Visual Arts in New York City.

Amelia Earhart was born on July 24, 1897, in Atchison, Kansas. She was the daughter of a lawyer and a social worker. She was a pioneer in aviation, and was the first woman to fly solo across the Atlantic Ocean. She disappeared in 1937 while attempting to fly around the world.

Charles Lindbergh was born in Detroit, Michigan, on February 4, 1902. He was the first person to fly solo across the Atlantic Ocean. Lindbergh was a pilot, inventor, and author. He was awarded the Congressional Medal of Honor in 1927. Lindbergh was also a member of the U.S. House of Representatives from 1943 to 1977. He died on August 26, 1974.

Born in Beijing, China, in 1963, Jet Li is a Chinese actor and martial artist. He started his career as a martial arts performer, and later became a movie star. He has appeared in over 100 movies, and has won many awards, including the Hong Kong Film Award for Best Actor. Yo is a rapper from New York City. He is known for his single "Yo! (Excuse Me Miss)," which was released in 1996. Yo was born in 1976 and grew up in the Bronx. Cleopatra was the last pharaoh of Ancient Egypt. She was the daughter of Ptolemy XII and Cleopatra V. Cleopatra was married to her brother, Ptolemy XIII, and then to Mark Antony. She was the mother of Caesarion, who was the last pharaoh of Ancient Egypt. Cleopatra was a very powerful ruler, and she was known for her beauty. She was also known for her intelligence and her political skills. Cleopatra was a very influential ruler, and she is still remembered today.

Mary Baker Eddy was born in 1821 in New Hampshire. She was the daughter of a farmer and a schoolteacher. She was a sickly child, and suffered from a variety of ailments. She was also a very religious child, and was deeply influenced by the teachings of the New England Transcendentalists. In 1866, she founded the Christian Science Church, which is based on the belief that all disease is caused by a lack of spiritual understanding. She wrote the book 'Science and Health with Key to the Scriptures,' which is the primary text of the Christian Science Church. She died in 1910.

Rafael Nadal was born in Manacor, Mallorca, Spain, on June 3, 1986. He is a professional tennis player, and is currently ranked world No. 1. Nadal is the only male player to win the French Open and Wimbledon in the same year. He has won 14 Grand Slam singles titles, and has been ranked world No. 1 by the Association of Tennis Professionals for a record 163 weeks. Nadal has won 23 ATP World Tour Masters 1000 titles, the most in the Open Era. He has won a record eight French Open titles, and is the only player to win the same Grand Slam tournament eight times. Nadal has won a record 32 ATP World Tour Masters 1000 singles titles, and is the only player to win the same Masters 1000 tournament eight times.

Roger Federer is a Swiss professional tennis player. He was born in 1981 in Basel, Switzerland. He is currently ranked world No. 3 by the Association of Tennis Professionals. He has won 17 Grand Slam singles titles, the most in history for a male player. He has won a record 8 Wimbledon titles, 5 Australian Open titles, 5 US Open titles, and 1 French Open title. He has also won a gold medal at the 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing.

Petra Cortright was born in 1986 in California. She is a video artist and a painter. She is known for her work with digital media. Cortright's work has been exhibited in galleries and museums around the world. She is currently based in Los Angeles.

Wolfgang Puck was born in Austria in 1949. He moved to the United States in 1973, and opened his first restaurant, Spago, in 1982. Puck has since opened several other restaurants, including Chinois on Main, and Wolfgang Puck Bar & Grill. He has also written several cookbooks, and has appeared on several television shows.

Christopher Nolan was born in London, England, on July 30, 1970. He is a British film director, screenwriter, and producer. Nolan is best known for directing the Batman trilogy, The Dark Knight, and Inception. He has won numerous awards, including the Academy Award for Best Original Screenplay for The Dark Knight.

Jenny Holzer was born in 1950 in Gallipolis, Ohio. She is an American conceptual artist, known for her large-scale public installations. She studied at Ohio University and the Rhode Island School of Design. In 1977, she moved to New York City, where she began her career as a conceptual artist. Her first public installation was Truisms, a series of posters with aphorisms, which were displayed in the streets of New York. In 1982, she began her series of Inflammatory Essays, which were also displayed in the streets. In 1989, she began her series of Truisms, which were displayed in public spaces. In 1990, she began her series of Projections, which were displayed in public spaces. In 1994, she began her series of Lustmord, which were displayed in public spaces.

Sol LeWitt was born in 1928 in Hartford, Connecticut. He was a pioneer of Conceptual Art, and is considered one of the most influential artists of the 20th century. LeWitt's work is characterized by his use of geometric shapes and lines, and his use of color. He is best known for his wall drawings, which are created by the artist, and then executed by other artists. LeWitt died in 2007.

Zhang Yiming is a Chinese entrepreneur and the founder of the social media platform, WeChat. He is also the founder of the Tencent Holdings Limited, a Chinese multinational investment holding company. Zhang Yiming was born in 1971 in Shenzhen, China. He graduated from the University of Electronic Science and Technology of China in 1993. He started his career as a software engineer at the Tencent Holdings Limited. In 2000, he became the president of Tencent. In 2013, he was named as one of the 50 most powerful people in the world by Forbes.

Born in 1965, Robert Downey Jr. is an American actor. He is best known for his role as Tony Stark in the 'Iron Man' series.
